    <avalancheActivity>
      <highlights>Moist and wet avalanches are the main danger.</highlights>
      <comment>In some localities 2 to 5 cm of snow fell in the past few hours above approximately 2500 m. Today the weather will be cloudy. Above approximately 2500 m: Some snow will fall today in some localities. &lt;br/> &lt;br/> These weather conditions from the early morning will give rise to moistening of the snowpack in all aspects between approximately 2100 and 2700 m. As the penetration by moisture increases moist snow slides and avalanches are possible, but they can reach medium size in isolated cases. This applies especially on steep slopes at high altitude, and on very steep west, north and east facing slopes at low and intermediate altitudes.</comment>
    </avalancheActivity>
